                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of leaf, a note on simony in a contemporary hand; below, a table in a different contemporary hand listing the number of chapters for each biblical book included in the Historia scholastica; next to this, another table, in the same hand, listing the ages of members of Adam's, Sem's and Abraham's respective family tree.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised bands and endbands. Pin clasps with leather straps. Metal corner and centre bosses. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in brown ink on a paper label: <quote>N<hi rend="super">o</hi> 48.</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 171</quote>; in brown ink on a paper label: <quote>e. 30. 5. 7.</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="310" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="230" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="95" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>The leather is heavily worn (torn and stitched at <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>) and the cover riddled with wormholes. Endbands visible. Centre front and lower back corner boss missing. Original straps and clasps missing; bottom leather strap (modern) severed.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1401">15th century</origDate>. Origin unknown.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Acquisition date unknown. It is uncertain whether the item listed on p. 53 of Vossius's catalogue of 1651 (U 202:1) refers to this or some other manuscript. The manuscript is listed as no. <quote>48</quote> in the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e), and as <quote>e. 30. 5. 7</quote> in Hammarsköld's catalogue from the 19th century (U 133; both signa found on the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>).</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
