                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Table of contents</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Table of contents, divided and keyed to the text by biblical book, section number, and chapter rubric.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: guidelines but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="5r" to="226r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102566"> Petrus Comestor </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Historia scholastica</title>
                                <incipit>REuerendo patri et domino suo Gylelmo dei gratia Sennonensi Archiepiscopo Petrus seruus christi presbyter Trecensis vitam bonam et exitum beatum </incipit>
                                <explicit>et in loco magis honorabili scilicet in cathacumbis</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Two sections of Comestor's text have been mixed up and transposed: on <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>, in the middle of the chapter listed as <quote>De dispersione filiorum Noe</quote>, at <quote>etiam plane prophetauit</quote> (Migne col. 1088C), the scribe skips part of the text - from <quote>Et predixit discipulo suo</quote> (Migne col. 1088C) to <quote>mortuus est in Haran</quote> (Migne col. 1091D), which is inserted instead on <locus from="26r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/>, with the transposition noted in the margin by a second hand. At <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>, the scribe has instead inserted the section beginning in the middle of the chapter designated as <quote>De labore Rebece in partu geminorum</quote> at <quote>et concepit mulier</quote> (Migne col. 1109D) and ending on <locus from="19r" to="19r" scheme="folios"/> with <quote>Serapis nominatus est</quote> (Migne, col. 1112D); this transposition is also
                                        noted in the margin on <locus from="19r" to="19r" scheme="folios"/>, at the end of the displaced section, and on <locus from="27r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/>, where the correct sequence of the text is resumed; on both <locus from="19r" to="19r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="27r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/>, the last 6 lines of the misplaced section are written by a second hand on top of the earlier, erased text.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="170r" to="172v" scheme="folios"/>: guidelines and part of running titles but no text.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="226v" to="226v" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                </note>
                                <colophon>
                                    <locus from="226r" to="226r" scheme="folios"/>Liber finitus scolastice intytulatus Hystorie <add place="inline">multum legenti conficeret fructum</add> Finitoque libro reddatur gloria christo AMEN Sunt tua consilia equissime iudex abyssus multa nec humane condicionis egent</colophon>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">PL</title>
                                    <citedRange from="198" to="198" unit="volume"/>
                                    <citedRange from="1053" to="1722" unit="column"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
