                                <p>
                                    <locus from="5r" to="226r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Explanations of words, indications of topics, and exegetical notes (e.g. <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>); nota marks and the occasional manicule (e.g. <locus from="125r" to="125v" scheme="folios"/>) <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="19r" to="19r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="27r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/>; annotations in pencil by a modern hand noting the displacement of text (using the earlier, crossed out foliation) and with references to Migne.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="169v" to="170r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A loose piece of scrap paper with contemporary writing on one side, probably used as a bookmark.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink. Chapter rubrics in red. Capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: plain opening initial <quote>R</quote> over 8 lines in red ink with flourishing in brown ink extending into the margin.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="173r" scheme="folios"/>: plain book initials in red ink over 4-7 lines, several with flourishing in brown extending into margin (e.g. <locus from="149v" to="149v" scheme="folios"/>) and some with interior reserved shapes (e.g. <locus from="112v" to="112v" scheme="folios"/>); one missing (<locus from="90v" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5v" to="226r" scheme="folios"/>: plain chapter initials over 2 lines, with some descenders beween 3 and 13 lines, in red ink, sometimes with penwork (e.g. <locus from="192v" to="192v" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                                </decoNote>
